<dl>
	<dt>Locate the dash icon in the launcher and press it to bring
up the Dash</dt>
	<dt>If the on screen keyboard does not appear, tap the input box
at the top of the Dash screen</dt>
	<dt>Using the on screen keyboard, start typing the word
'terminal'</dt>
                <dd>After you get about as far as 'term', you will 
robably see an icon for 'Terminal' just below the text entry field</dd>
        <dt>Tap the 'Terminal' icon when it appears</dt>
	<dt>If the on screen keyboard is not present, tap inside the
terminal window near where the cursor is blinking</dt>
                <dd>The on screen keyboard should come up</dd>
	<dt>Using the on screen keyboard, enter a few basic commands to
sanity check the shell such as 'ls', 'pwd', 'uname -a'</dt>
